  "prompt": "3 digit no unit digit, ten digit and hundred digit their ratio 3:5:7 if the difference of original number and \u0155eversing the digit is 396 find the no?",
  "response": "Let the three-digit number be represented as \\( xyz \\), where \\( x \\), \\( y \\), and \\( z \\) are the hundred, ten, and unit digits respectively.\n\nFrom the problem, the ratio of the digits is given as:\n\n- \\( x : y : z = 3 : 5 : 7 \\)\n\nLet us represent the digits in terms of a variable \\( k \\):\n\n- \\( x = 3k \\)\n- \\( y = 5k \\)\n- \\( z = 7k \\)\n\nSince these are digits, they must be in the range of 0 to 9. Therefore, the maximum value for \\( k \\) must ensure that \\( 3k \\), \\( 5k \\), and \\( 7k \\) are each valid single-digit numbers.\n\nConsidering \\( z = 7k \\):\n- The maximum \\( z\\) can be is 9, thus:\n  \\[\n  7k \\leq 9 \\implies k \\leq \\frac{9}{7} \\approx 1.2857\n  \\]\nThe largest integer \\( k \\) can take is 1.\n\nIf \\( k = 1 \\):\n- \\( x = 3(1) = 3 \\)\n- \\( y = 5(1) = 5 \\)\n- \\( z = 7(1) = 7 \\)\n\nThus, the three-digit number \\( xyz = 357 \\).\n\nNext, we find the reverse of this number, which is \\( 753 \\).\n\nNow we check the difference:\n\\[\n753 - 357 = 396\n\\]\n\nSince this holds true, we conclude that the three-digit number is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{357}\n\\]",
